fields.text:
i decided i would paint a still life. in oil of course. and on canvas no less. a lot of people do it, and i am no better. i do have a geranium on my window, which, many might think, is a very mundane subject to paint, especially if it is placed against a uniform light background. i am going to try at least, and if i ever make it, we will see what comes out. bear with me, dear reader.

and one more thing, i could not resist putting up a quote from a song by Vladimir Vysotsky (see wikipedia.org). for those who can read russian.

{% with self.plates.all.0 as p %} {% with p.get_display as d %} {% endwith %} {% endwith %} У нее, у нее на окошке герань,
У нее, у нее занавески в разводах.
А у меня, у меня на окне ни хера,
Только пыль, только старая пыль на комодах.
